The paper deals with a distributed estimation problem in sensor networks with intermittent measurements and fading channels, which is a typical problem in information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). The proposed algorithm is fully distributed, which is a characteristic of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also presents a performance-oriented design of the algorithm parameters, which involves optimization and numerical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the simulation results demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm, which is a common theme in signal processing (cs.SI).
